      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Linda Ty-Casper (1931- ) is a Filipino novelist.  Born in Manila, capital of the Philippines, she grew up in Malabon and holds degrees from the University of the Philippines and Harvard University Law School.  Her husband, Leonard Casper, is a professor emeritus of Boston College who is also a critic of Philippine Literature.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Linda Ty-Casper Manuscripts</emph> consists of manuscripts of her writings, both books and short stories.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
